Thank you @sawientertainment & @_productofculture_ for bringing together this community of women. I was really moved to see so many South Asian women in our industry in one room. I wish I had role models like this when I was growing up, when I didn’t think being an actress or producer was even an option.

Excited to continue championing each other, building together, and lifting up the next generation. Again, well done SAWIE and PoC on a great event this Oscars weekend! Chai from @lachaicart was on point. ☕️

Happy birthday Payal!!

What an incredible weekend full of love, music, and dance.  @payal is one of those gems who finds the light in every person she meets, encouraging us all to be the best version of ourselves because she truly believes we are all capable of greatness. She embodies compassion, dedication, and inspiration, and it makes me warm and fuzzy to think we’ve been friends for over 15 years! From dance teammate to roommate to my maid of honor and now fellow mom - I can’t imagine what my life would have been like without her friendship. Happy birthday Payal! I love you! And thanks @nickpujji for organizing such an epic weekend!

📸 @shivalry_inc

@politesocietymovie opens in theaters TONIGHT!! I had the chance to see a screening this week and I can’t say enough how incredible this film is. It is the perfect blend of action and absurdity with delightfully irreverent performances by the perfectly cast @priyakansara and @rituarya. Well done to director Nida Manzoor. A game changing movie I can’t wait to see again and again and eventually show my daughters when they are old enough :). Go to theaters and support their opening weekend! I’ll buy two tickets for the first person who DMs me saying they will go to a showing tonight. 🍿

Huge congratulations to this superstar, @zarnagarg. A mom of 3, an immigrant, a bonafide hustler, a joy, and an inspiration - Zarna landed her very own standup special with Amazon and it is now LIVE. Check it out!! Rate, comment, engage - these things matter. Zarna, I’m so happy for you!

We’ve had an instant print camera sitting around for about a year now and finally decided to use it this summer, instead of taking hundreds of photos of the same thing and ultimately never doing anything with them….

I told my girls we were allowed only 1-3 photos daily. We captured things in the moment with no re-do’s and that actually made things really special, because each photo felt pure in spirit and had a story behind them.

There is something so much nice about seeing a photo in its physical form. Remember those albums our parents had??

Ps - thanks to all our friends who were a part of this!

#summer2023 #familyphotography  #kodakprintomatic
